<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-07-01T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-07-01T18:00:00-05:00" n="543" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d543">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.3531/1534: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Armour</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-07-01T19:00:00-04:00">July 1, 1940—7
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>128. Department’s 122, June 22, 1940. Mr. Harry Hawkins, Chief of the
                            Division of Commercial Treaties and Agreements, and Mr. George
                            Luthringer of the Office of the Economic Adviser, have been selected for
                            the mission. Please ascertain and inform the Department when these
                            officers should arrive in Argentina.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>